article.headline: James Madison 74, Delaware 64
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Daniel Freeman scored 20 of his 24 points in the second half, including 6 in a 13-0 run right out of intermission, and James Madison snapped a 12-game losing streak with a 74-64 victory against Delaware on Monday night. The Dukes (4-17, 1-12) trailed 41-30 at halftime, but rallied behind Freeman to beat the Blue Hens for the first time in 10 meetings. Juwann James, Jomo Belfor and Ray Barbosa scored 13 for James Madison. Belfor added seven rebounds and five assists. Delaware (6-16, 2-11) took the big halftime lead by shooting nearly 63 percent behind Harding Nana's 18 points in the half, then both went cold. The Blue Hens made only four field goals in the second half, shooting 22 percent, and Nana finished with 25 points. Rulon Washington added 14 points and Calvin Cannon 12 for the Hens.
